1. Još se nisam *usudio* da mu kažem istinu. (I haven't *dared* to tell him the truth yet.)
2. On *se usudio* da priđe opasnom psu. (He *dared* to approach a dangerous dog.)
3. Ako *usudite* da pokušate, možete to i ostvariti. (If you *dare* to try, you can achieve it.)
4. Zato što se *usudio* da sanja, postao je ono što jeste. (Because he *dared* to dream, he became what he is.)
5. Ona nije *usudila* da otvori pismo dok nije bila sama. (She didn't *dare* to open the letter until she was alone.)
6. Moramo se *usuditi* da učinimo nešto drugačije ako želimo promjenu. (We must *dare* to do something different if we want change.)
7. Njegova hrabrost i *usud* privukli su mnoge obožavatelje. (His courage and *daring* attracted many fans.)
8. Čovjek mora imati *usuda* da se suoči sa svojim strahovima. (A man must have *the courage* to face his fears.)